I filled my pants
in my first battle too.

84
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:26,759
No one is born a hero.
Here, take these.

85
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,879
Their owner won't need them.

86
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:32,399
He did more than sprain his neck.

87
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,359
Agrippa, I've been looking for you.

88
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,199
We wanted to see the Admiral.

89
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:41,559
Who is that?

90
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,719
Someone with battle-browned britches.

91
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,279
The Prince of Navarre.

92
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,839
I am delighted to meet you, Prince.

93
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:58,599
- Who are you?
- I am the Prince of Navarre.

94
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,919
Forgive me, Prince. I didn't know.

95
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,319
And who are you?

96
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:09,079
Two poor poets whose verses
serve no one in such times.

97
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,879
He is Agrippa d'Aubigné
and I'm Guillaume du Bartas.

98
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:15,759
You, a poet? That's news to me!

99
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:18,199
And you, a clothes thief.
That's nothing new.

100
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:19,639
He's right!

101
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:22,759
Ideal company for a prince.

102
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:34,319
I want to go home, Beauvois.

103
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:39,839
This tent is your home, my Prince.

104
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:43,839
For many years thereafter,
this mean tent wouId be my home.

105
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:46,839
War and death wouId be my escorts.

106
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:51,279
And hatred for everything CathoIic.

107
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,759
This is the Catholics' doing.

108
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:30,919
I want to eat you up.

109
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,599
My Prince, Prince Henry!

110
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:47,799
Your mother, Queen Jeanne, is coming.

111
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,279
She's here.

112
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,399
It reeks of fish in your tent.

113
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:01,439
And garlic. That's me.

114
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,079
Come to the Admiral's tent.

115
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,039
Word from Paris.

116
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,999
They made an offer.

117
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,279
Because they fear us.

118
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:30,279
As they should.

119
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:33,319
Catherine wants peace
with the Huguenots.

120
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,039
The slaughter can end.

121
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,559
We agree.

122
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,439
That's new.

123
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:45,599
But as a sign of reconciliation,
she expects a sacrifice.

124
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:48,719
The Queen of France

125
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,319
